  "response_text": "A young blonde woman enters a warmly lit apartment, wearing a long olive-green coat over a white blouse and dark trousers. Beside her is an open wardrobe alcove with coats hanging inside, and a mirror reflects part of her face and the room. The atmosphere is soft and intimate, with candles and a single red rose visible on a console table.\n\nOn the wooden floor, a small cream-colored folded card stands like a tent, and in front of it lies a red Lindt Lindor truffle wrapped in shiny foil with clear twisted ends. The woman’s hand reaches down, gently picks up the red-wrapped chocolate, then moves to the folded card. She lifts the card as if discovering a note left for her.\n\nShe bends near a sideboard topped with a glowing oval lamp, candles, books, a vase with a red flower, and decorative objects. After picking up the note, she stands and reads it. In the hallway beyond her, more small cream cards appear spaced along the floor, forming a trail toward a softly lit room framed by an archway and sheer curtains.\n\nFacing forward now, the woman holds the cream note in one hand and the red Lindor truffle in the other. Her expression softens into a small, pleased smile. She then unwraps the chocolate; a close view shows the red foil wrapper decorated with white floral patterns and gold Lindt branding. She brings the chocolate to her lips, closes her eyes, and eats it with a calm, satisfied expression.\n\nThe imagery shifts to a glossy close-up of melted milk chocolate flowing into a rounded chocolate shell, forming smooth ripples and a shiny surface. A Lindt chocolatier appears in a bright kitchen setting, wearing a white chef’s jacket and tall white chef’s hat with Lindt embroidery. He carefully lifts a wire whisk coated in melted chocolate, letting thick ribbons of chocolate pour down as he watches with focused attention.\n\nBack in the apartment, the woman reaches the end of the trail and meets a man standing in the arched doorway. He has a bald head and wears a light sweater with dark trousers. They move into an embrace, holding each other closely in the softly lit room, with candles glowing nearby and curtains diffusing the light behind them.\n\nThe commercial ends on a red product display. A red Lindt Lindor package stands beside a large red heart-shaped Lindor gift box decorated with small hearts and floral accents. On the right, white and gold text reads “Lindt,” “Master Swiss Chocolatier Since 1845,” and the slogan “Melt the One You Love.”",
